  "prompt": "How can I save images in Quora?",
  "response": "To save images on Quora, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Using a Computer:**\n   - Open the Quora page with the image you want to save.\n   - Right-click on the image.\n   - Select \"Save image as...\" from the context menu.\n   - Choose the destination folder on your computer where you want to save the image and click \"Save.\"\n\n2. **Using a Mobile Device:**\n   - Open the Quora app or website on your mobile device.\n   - Find the image you wish to save.\n   - Tap and hold the image until a menu appears.\n   - Select \"Download image\u201d or \u201cSave image\" from the options presented. The image will be saved to your device\u2019s gallery or photo app.\n\nKeep in mind that you should respect copyright and privacy laws when saving and using images from Quora or any other platform. Always make sure to credit the content creator where applicable.",
